"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The set_context() and set_style() functions are used to customize seaborn styles, but they do not have an rc parameter. Instead, the correct parameter to use for passing a dictionary of parameters is the rc parameter of the set_theme() function.\",\n  \"patch\": \"8c8\\n< sns.set_context(rc=scale_dict)\\n---\\n> sns.set_theme(context='notebook', rc=scale_dict)\\n14c14\\n< sns.set_style(rc=style_dict)\\n---\\n> sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', rc=style_dict)\\n\"\n}"